From 990ec243cb77c682e12bb84c98906880536132aa Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Date: Mon, 25 Nov 2019 17:56:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] pinctrl: baytrail: Keep pointer to struct device instead of its container
Git-commit: 990ec243cb77c682e12bb84c98906880536132aa
Patch-mainline: v5.6-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-12730

There is no need to keep pointer to struct platform_device, which is container
of struct device, because the latter is what have been used everywhere outside
of ->probe() path. In any case we may derive pointer to the container when
needed.

Acked-by: Hans de Goede <hdegoede@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Mika Westerberg <mika.westerberg@linux.intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Linus Walleij <linus.walleij@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/pinctrl/intel/pinctrl-baytrail.c | 58 ++++++++++++++++----------------
 1 file changed, 29 insertions(+), 29 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/pinctrl/intel/pinctrl-baytrail.c b/drivers/pinctrl/intel/pinctrl-baytrail.c
index 0e131d2e094d..6e79138fc7f5 100644
